To constitute a State Level Committee for procurement of various types of machinery for diagnosis and treatment of cancer in medical colleges and hospitals and other institutions.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Medical Education and Pharmaceuticals,
Government Decisions, No.: Committee-2025 / Q. No.531 / Proceedings-I,
Gokuldas Tejpal Hospital Complex, New G.T. Complex,
9th Floor, Mantralaya, Mumbai - 400 001
Date: November 27, 2025.
Read: Government Decisions, Industries, Power and Labour Department, No. Bhankhas 2014 / Q. No.82 / Part- / Industry - 4, dated 1st December, 2016

Introduction: There is an urgent need to provide state-of-the-art equipment required for cancer diagnosis and treatment in government medical colleges and hospitals in the state. The increasing number of cancer and other disease cases necessitates the availability of high-quality equipment for continuous improvement in diagnosis, treatment, and follow-up services.

Accordingly, the government continues to receive proposals from institutions for the purchase of such equipment. There is a considerable discrepancy between these received equipment purchase offers. It was under the consideration of the government to constitute a state-level committee to make recommendations to the government after considering all aspects together and fairly while procuring these equipment.

Government Decision: In accordance with the provisions of paragraph No. 2.9.2 of the Revised Procurement Manual published under the Government Decision dated 01.12.2016 of the Department of Industries, Power and Labour, the following Central Procurement Committee is being constituted for the procurement of various types of machinery and equipment for the diagnosis and treatment of cancer for all the institutions under the jurisdiction of the Department.
The composition of the committee for cancer machinery is as follows: -

In pursuance of this meeting, proposals are submitted to the Department for approval to accept the minimum bid price of the bidders selected for tendering the machinery and allow them to place orders.

9. These proposals are required to be examined in accordance with Government Rules, Financial Institutions Rules and the prevailing procurement procedures, for which separate and in-depth scrutiny is required.
Accordingly, the following Committee is being constituted to examine the minimum received tender proposals: -
The scope of the committee is 1. To conduct technical, financial and procedural review of LY tender proposals received from the Directorate.
2. Verify that all the documents in the tender process are in compliance with the government rules.
3. Submit the report and recommendations of the Committee to the Department after examination.
4. To make recommendations to the Government on the procurement order only after receipt of the report of the Committee.
